description:
## Problem
Path parameters are missing from endpoint detail for specs that define parameters as $ref references. GitHub API defines path params like {owner} and {repo} as $ref: "#/components/parameters/owner" but phyllotaxis skips all $ref parameters.

Endpoint detail for GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls shows only query parameters. Path params are invisible even though they have useful descriptions and constraints in the spec.

## Root Cause
In src/commands/resources.rs:684-688, the merge_parameters function skips $ref parameters:
```rust
let param = match param_ref {
    openapiv3::ReferenceOr::Item(p) => p,
    openapiv3::ReferenceOr::Reference { .. } => continue,  // <-- Skips ALL $ref params
};
```

## Fix
Resolve parameter $refs by looking them up in components.parameters. Something like:
```rust
let param = match param_ref {
    openapiv3::ReferenceOr::Item(p) => p,
    openapiv3::ReferenceOr::Reference { reference } => {
        // Resolve from components.parameters
        let param_name = reference.strip_prefix("#/components/parameters/")?;
        // Look up in api.components.as_ref()?.parameters
        // ...
        continue; // if resolution fails
    }
};
```

## Files to Change
- src/commands/resources.rs:684-688 (merge_parameters function - resolve $ref parameters)

## Success Criteria
- `phyllotaxis resources repos GET /repos/{owner}/{repo} --spec /tmp/github-api.json` shows Path Parameters section with owner and repo (with descriptions)
- Path params visible in both text and JSON output
- Existing inline parameter handling unaffected
- cargo test passes

## Problem
Endpoints returning arrays (e.g. GET /pet/findByStatus -> Pet[], GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls -> pull-request[]) show no response type. Text output shows bare "200 Successful operation" with no "-> Type[]". JSON output shows schema_ref: null.

## Root Cause
In src/commands/resources.rs lines 616-620, the extract_responses function only resolves schema_ref when the response schema is a direct $ref reference:
```rust
let schema_ref = media.schema.as_ref().and_then(|sr| match sr {
    openapiv3::ReferenceOr::Reference { reference } => {
        spec::schema_name_from_ref(reference).map(|s| s.to_string())
    }
    _ => None,  // <-- Array schemas (ReferenceOr::Item) fall through here
});
```
When the response schema is `type: array` with `items: {$ref: "#/components/schemas/Pet"}`, it's a ReferenceOr::Item (an inline schema), not a Reference. The code returns None.

## Fix
In the `_ => None` arm, check if the schema is an array type with items that are a $ref. If so, extract the ref name and format as "TypeName[]". Something like:
```rust
openapiv3::ReferenceOr::Item(schema) => {
    match &schema.schema_kind {
        openapiv3::SchemaKind::Type(openapiv3::Type::Array(arr)) => {
            arr.items.as_ref().and_then(|items| match items.as_ref() {
                openapiv3::ReferenceOr::Reference { reference } => {
                    spec::schema_name_from_ref(reference)
                        .map(|s| format!("{}[]", s))
                }
                _ => None,
            })
        }
        _ => None,
    }
}
```

Also update the JSON output in src/render/json.rs to include the array indicator in schema_ref.

## Files to Change
- src/commands/resources.rs:616-620 (extract_responses - resolve array item refs)
- src/render/json.rs (ensure schema_ref carries the "[]" suffix for array responses)

## Success Criteria
- `phyllotaxis resources pet GET /pet/findByStatus --spec /tmp/petstore.json` shows "200 -> Pet[]"
- `phyllotaxis resources pet GET /pet/findByStatus --json --spec /tmp/petstore.json` shows schema_ref: "Pet[]"
- Same for GitHub: `resources pulls GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls` shows "-> pull-request[]"
- Existing non-array responses (e.g. GET /pet/{petId} -> Pet) still work
- cargo test passes
